    "plan_content": "Here's a summary of the plan I've written:\n\n## Plan: Add `Bun.INI` Namespace\n\n**6 files to touch (1 new, 5 edits):**\n\n### Step 1 — CREATE `src/bun.js/api/INIObject.zig`\nSelf-contained INI implementation modelled after `JSON5Object.zig`:\n- **`create()`** — builds a JS object with `parse` and `stringify` functions\n- **`parse()`** — line-by-line parser: skips `#`/`;` comments, handles `[section]` headers (→ nested JS objects on root), handles `key = value` pairs with whitespace trim, coerces `\"true\"`/`\"false\"`/numeric strings to JS types, throws `SyntaxError` on malformed input\n- **`stringify()`** — two-pass: emit top-level scalar `key = value` first, then `[section]\\nkey = value` for top-level objects; uses `wtf.StringBuilder`\n\n### Step 2 — EDIT `src/bun.js/api.zig` (~line 33)\nAdd: `pub const INIObject = @import(\"./api/INIObject.zig\");`\n\n### Step 3 — EDIT `src/bun.js/api/BunObject.zig` (3 hunks)\n- ~line 66: `pub const INI = toJSLazyPropertyCallback(Bun.getINIObject);`\n- ~line 1273: `pub fn getINIObject(...) { return INIObject.create(globalThis); }`\n- ~line 2079: `const INIObject = bun.api.INIObject;`\n\n### Step 4 — EDIT `src/bun.js/bindings/BunObject+exports.h` (~line 11)\nAdd `macro(INI)` between `macro(Glob)` and `macro(JSON5)` (alphabetical)\n\n### Step 5 — EDIT `src/bun.js/bindings/BunObject.cpp` (~line 963)\nAdd hash table row: `INI    BunObject_lazyPropCb_wrap_INI    DontDelete|PropertyCallback`\n\n### Step 6 — EDIT `packages/bun-types/bun.d.ts` (after line ~821)\nAdd `namespace INI { parse(input: string): Record<string, any>; stringify(input: Record<string, any>): string; }` with full JSDoc + examples",
